    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2011-03-10</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2011-03-15T21:32:42Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>EEOICPA Amendment Act of 2011 - Amends the Energy Employees Occupational Illness Compensation Program Act of 2000 to require the President to establish an Advisory Board on Toxic Substances and Worker Health.</p> <p>Requires the Board to advise the Secretary of Labor, the Secretary of Energy (DOE), and the Secretary of Health and Human Services (HHS) on the review and approval of the site exposure matrix (SEM) used to determine the eligibility of DOE contractor employee claims for compensation for illnesses resulting from exposure to toxic substances.</p> ]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
